TATlit — licensing
==================

1. Model weights, tokenizer, and code
--------------------------------------
The model weights (hosted at https://huggingface.co/ilchats/TATlit), the
SentencePiece tokenizer in tokenizer/, and all source code in this repository
are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0
International License (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).

  Human-readable summary: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/
  Full legal code:        https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/legalcode

  You are free to share and adapt this material for non-commercial purposes,
  provided you give appropriate credit and distribute your contributions under
  the same license.

2. TatBLiMP benchmark
---------------------
The TatBLiMP benchmark is not included in this repository. It is distributed
separately at https://github.com/ilchats/TatBLiMP under the terms given there.

3. Training corpus
------------------
The training corpus is not released. It is withheld on stewardship grounds for a
minoritized language's literary heritage. A full datasheet with per-document
provenance is available on reasonable request.

Attribution
-----------
Ilshat Saetov, Dmitry Gaynullin. 2026. Thanks to the Siblings: Bootstrapping a
Native Tatar Language Model from a Cyrillic Qypchaq Pool.
